AU Lieberman-J.  Rodbard-S.
TI Low blood pressure in young adults with cystic fibrosis: an effect
   of chronic salt loss in sweat?.
SO Ann-Intern-Med. 1975 Jun. 82(6). P 806-8.
MJ BLOOD-PRESSURE.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: pp.  SWEATING.
   WATER-ELECTROLYTE-BALANCE.
MN ADOLESCENCE.  ADULT.  BLOOD-PRESSURE-DETERMINATION.
   CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: me.  EXERTION.  FEMALE.  HUMAN.  MALE.  SEX-FACTORS.
AB Young adults with cystic fibrosis have lower blood pressures than
   control subjects of similar age and sex. The low blood pressure may
   be related to the excessive loss of salt in the sweat of these
   patients. A beneficial effect of the cystic fibrosis gene may be
   protection against developing hypertension in both the homozygous and
   heterozygous states, especially if the heterozygote has borderline
   elevation of sweat electrolytes.
